A directory in the hierarchy is missing. That's misleading.

It's written:
{panel}
There was an error creating the Bamboo Home directory. The most common cause is you haven't specified it.
To fix this, simply set the *bamboo.home* property in the file */WEB-INF/classes/bamboo-init.properties* to your chosen bamboo home directory.{panel}

It should be written:
{panel}
There was an error creating the Bamboo Home directory. The most common cause is you haven't specified it.
To fix this, simply set the *bamboo.home* property in the file *<Bamboo installation directory>/atlassian-bamboo/WEB-INF/classes/bamboo-init.properties* to your chosen bamboo home directory.{panel}

This issue is something similar to the bug affecting MSBUILD at BAM-13608

The options is something like:
{code}
/D:arg="/xml:Result.xml /exclude:Nightly" /D:TestsPath="src\Tests"
{code} 

The build fails with the message 
{code}
Unknown argument '/exclude:Nightly'
{code}

the space has made bamboo to view it as a separate argument.

*Workaround*
Replace the quotes with single quotes. Something like below will work

{code}
/D:arg='/xml:Result.xml /exclude:Nightly' /D:TestsPath='src\Tests'
{code}

{quote}
Say for example we have some job which runs style checks on code download from a repository. We would want to run those same style checks on many different repositories. Is there a way I can define a job and share it between multiple build plans (one per repository)?
I know it's possible to clone build plans, but then if I want to update the job I have to do it in each cloned build plan. If the job was shared than I could update it once and it would take effect in all build plans.
{quote}
